nodes.bodyText:
The first time a buffer is released, largerBuffer will be set unconditionally. The second time it's released, smallerBuffer will be set unconditionally. If the second buffer is larger than the first one, we end up with the variables tracking the opposite buffers they should be tracking:
PagesSerdeContext context = new PagesSerdeContext();

context.releaseBuffer(context.acquireBuffer(5));
context.releaseBuffer(context.acquireBuffer(10));

System.out.println("smaller: " + context.smallerBuffer.length);
System.out.println("larger:  " + context.largerBuffer.length);
produces:
smaller: 10
larger:  5

